The paper discusses security and privacy issues related to network traffic generated by mobile devices, which suggests that it belongs to the category of Computer Science and Cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper focuses on network traffic analysis, which is a subfield of Computer Networks and Communications (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of multi-purpose applications on mobile devices, which falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the challenges and possible directions for future research on mobile traffic analysis, which suggests that it belongs to the category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mobile devices in the Internet of Things (IoT), which suggests that it belongs to the category of Systems and Control (cs.SI).
